Smart Parking System
Problem Statement:
Finding parking space in cities is difficult due to the absence of
real-time slot monitoring.
Objective:
Design a parking management system that uses IR sensors to
detect free slots and display them on a dashboard.
Requirements:
Arduino Uno or NodeMCU
IR Proximity Sensors (1 per slot)
LCD Display or Web Dashboard
Jumper wires, breadboard
Wi-Fi module (ESP8266)
Expected Outcome:
A working smart parking model that detects empty slots and
updates their status in real-time on a digital display or web
interface.

